.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
Creates an Oracle Cloud VMware Solution software\-defined data center (SDDC).
.sp
Use the \fI\%WorkRequest\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/api/#/en/vmware/20200501/WorkRequest/\fP> operations to track the creation of the SDDC.
.sp
\fBImportant:\fP You must configure the SDDC’s networking resources with the security rules detailed in \fI\%Security Rules for Oracle Cloud VMware Solution SDDCs\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/iaas/Content/VMware/Reference/ocvssecurityrules.htm\fP>\&. Otherwise, provisioning the SDDC will fail. The rules are based on the requirements set by VMware.
.SH USAGE
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
oci ocvs sddc create [OPTIONS]
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH REQUIRED PARAMETERS
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-compartment\-id, \-c [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
The \fI\%OCID\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/Content/General/Concepts/identifiers.htm\fP> of the compartment to contain the SDDC.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-compute\-availability\-domain, \-\-ad [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
The availability domain to create the SDDC’s ESXi hosts in. For multi\-AD SDDC deployment, set to \fImulti\-AD\fP\&.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-esxi\-count [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
The number of ESXi hosts to create in the SDDC. You can add more hosts later (see \fI\%CreateEsxiHost\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/en-us/iaas/tools/oci-cli/latest/oci_cli_docs/cmdref/ocvs/esxi-host/create.html\fP>).
.sp
\fBNote:\fP If you later delete EXSi hosts from the SDDC to total less than 3, you are still billed for the 3 minimum recommended EXSi hosts. Also, you cannot add more VMware workloads to the SDDC until it again has at least 3 ESXi hosts.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-instance\-prefix [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
A prefix used in the name of each ESXi host and Compute instance in the SDDC. If this isn’t set, the SDDC’s \fIdisplayName\fP is used as the prefix.
.sp
For example, if the value is \fImySDDC\fP, the ESXi hosts are named \fImySDDC\-1\fP, \fImySDDC\-2\fP, and so on.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-nsx\-edge\-up1\-id [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
The \fI\%OCID\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/Content/General/Concepts/identifiers.htm\fP> of the VLAN to use for the NSX Edge Uplink 1 component of the VMware environment.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-nsx\-edge\-up2\-id [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
The \fI\%OCID\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/Content/General/Concepts/identifiers.htm\fP> of the VLAN to use for the NSX Edge Uplink 2 component of the VMware environment.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-nsx\-edge\-vtep\-id [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
The \fI\%OCID\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/Content/General/Concepts/identifiers.htm\fP> of the VLAN to use for the NSX Edge VTEP component of the VMware environment.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-nsx\-vtep\-id [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
The \fI\%OCID\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/Content/General/Concepts/identifiers.htm\fP> of the VLAN to use for the NSX VTEP component of the VMware environment.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-prov\-subnet\-id [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
The \fI\%OCID\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/Content/General/Concepts/identifiers.htm\fP> of the management subnet to use for provisioning the SDDC.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-ssh\-authorized\-keys [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
One or more public SSH keys to be included in the \fI~/.ssh/authorized_keys\fP file for the default user on each ESXi host. Use a newline character to separate multiple keys. The SSH keys must be in the format required for the \fIauthorized_keys\fP file
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-vmotion\-id [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
The \fI\%OCID\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/Content/General/Concepts/identifiers.htm\fP> of the VLAN to use for the vMotion component of the VMware environment.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-vmware\-version [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
The VMware software bundle to install on the ESXi hosts in the SDDC. To get a list of the available versions, use \fI\%ListSupportedVmwareSoftwareVersions\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/en-us/iaas/tools/oci-cli/latest/oci_cli_docs/cmdref/ocvs/sddc/vmware-versions.html\fP>\&.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-vsan\-id [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
The \fI\%OCID\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/Content/General/Concepts/identifiers.htm\fP> of the VLAN to use for the vSAN component of the VMware environment.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-\-vsphere\-id [text]
.UNINDENT
.sp
The \fI\%OCID\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/Content/General/Concepts/identifiers.htm\fP> of the VLAN to use for the vSphere component of the VMware environment.
